                <h1>Do you want to open a cocktail bar or do you already have one that isn't
                    working?</h1>
                <p class="divParagraph">
                    Then you've come to the right place. I offer my knowledge from many years of
                    experience around the best bars in the world to help you set up your bar in the
                    best way for your business.
                </p>
                <hr>
                <h1>What kind of services do I offer?</h1>
                <hr>
                <h2>Bar plan and set up.</h2>
                <p class="divParagraph">
                    I can plan and organize the bar in the best way according to HACCP standards,
                    ensuring it's workable for the bartenders and appealing to the clients.
                    <br>
                    Many bar owners don't know what a bar should look like to create a nice working
                    environment.
                    <br>
                    As a result, they may end up with a nice-looking bar but struggle to find good
                    bartenders to work for it because it's not comfortable to work.
                    <br>
                    So, bar planning, organization, and setup are very important fundamentals to
                    properly run the business.
                </p>
                <hr>
                <h2>List of bar tools and products.</h2>
                <p class="divParagraph">
                    Many bar owners or bartenders buy unnecessary items like many soft drinks,
                    syrups, or spirits that aren't really needed for the startup.
                    <br>
                    Ok, if you have a crazy amount of money to spend, also your target is premium
                    clients, then of course you buy the best.
                    <br>
                    But still, you will have to set up in the right way, exclusive way in this case.
                    <br>
                    You don't want people to buy bottles they can find in supermarkets.
                    <br>
                    What you really need for a startup is the minimum useful amount of stock where
                    the guest is happy and the owner doesn't spend a crazy amount of money on things
                    that will never be used or drunk.
                    <br>
                    It's a waste of money and we all know how having less waste, especially at the
                    beginning.
                    <br>
                    This can be a key point for your business to succeed together with good
                    marketing, good products and business strategies.
                    <br>
                    I can tell you that 99% of people really waste money when it comes to a startup.
                    <br>
                    I have seen many bar owners open and close because they have spent too much
                    money, and return of investments was very slow because of that they decided to
                    sell.
                    <br>
                    So, don't waste your time and money, call a professional bartender who knows
                    what to do.
                </p>
                <hr>
